Privacy Policy
Last Updated: [Date]

At DieanBot, we take your privacy seriously. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, disclose, and protect your information when you use our application (DieanBot). By using the App, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.

1. Information We Collect
We collect the following types of information:

a. Personal Information
We may collect personally identifiable information (PII) that you provide directly, such as:

Your name
Discord username and user ID
Any other information you voluntarily provide
b. Non-Personal Information
We may also collect non-personal information that cannot be used to identify you, including but not limited to:

App usage data
Device information (such as IP address, browser type, and operating system)
Cookies and similar technologies (where applicable)
2. How We Use Your Information
We use the information we collect for the following purposes:

To provide and maintain the App.
To improve, personalize, and enhance your experience.
To respond to your inquiries, feedback, or issues.
To communicate with you about updates, changes, or new features of the App.
To monitor and analyze usage patterns and trends.
3. Data Sharing and Disclosure
We do not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer your personal information to third parties without your consent, except in the following cases:

Service Providers: We may share your information with third-party service providers to help us operate the App or perform related services, provided they agree to keep your information confidential.
Legal Compliance: We may disclose your information if required by law, court order, or in response to a legal request.
4. Data Security
We are committed to protecting your information. We implement reasonable security measures to protect against unauthorized access, alteration, or disclosure of your personal information. However, no method of transmission over the internet or method of electronic storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.

5. Data Retention
We retain your personal information for as long as is necessary to provide you with the App and fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy. You may request the deletion of your data at any time by contacting us at dieannam177@gmail.com.

6. Your Rights
Depending on your location, you may have the following rights regarding your personal information:

The right to access your personal data.
The right to correct inaccurate information.
The right to request deletion of your data.
The right to object to or restrict certain data processing activities.
To exercise these rights, please contact us at dieannam177@gmail.com.

7. Third-Party Links
Our App may contain links to third-party websites or services. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of these third-party services. We recommend that you review the privacy policies of any third-party services you use.

